y duration-300" href="/diversity">Diversity &amp; Inclusion</a></div><div class="jsx-627b8ad5de6dab4e nav-link"><a class="mr-8 font-label hidden md:block hover:opacity-50 transition-opacity duration-300" href="/sustainability">Sustainability</a></div><div class="jsx-627b8ad5de6dab4e nav-link"><a class="mr-8 font-label hidden md:block hover:opacity-50 transition-opacity duration-300" href="/contact">Contact</a></div></nav><button class="jsx-627b8ad5de6dab4e ml-10 toggle-menu absolute top-6 right-6"><img src="/images/misc/menu-closed.svg" alt="Open Menu" class="jsx-627b8ad5de6dab4e"/></button></header><div class="bg-white"><main class="bg-white" style="opacity:0"><article class="px-2 md:px-6 py-10 md:py-12"><header class="flex px-2 md:px-0 md:pb-12 border-b flex-wrap items-center"><div class="md:w-6/12"><picture><img height="1080" width="1920" class="" loading="lazy" src="https://strapi-bus-eng-prod.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/Pansy_Luo_211698ad5b.jpg" alt=""/><sub class="mt-2"></sub></picture></div><div class="md:w-6/12 px-0 md:px-12 py-4 md:py-16 mx-auto max-w-titles small-body"><div class="font-small uppercase mb-4">Jan 29, 2024</div><h2>In The Spotlight: Pansy Luo</h2><div class="max-w-sm"><div class="rich-text">Condé Nast China’s Senior HR Manager Pansy Luo discusses Lunar New Year, the project she is most proud of and the first D&I offline training in the market.</div></div><div class="mt-4 md:mt-8 small-body flex flex-wrap"></div></div></header><div class="small-body text-black px-2 md:px-0 py-8 md:py-36 mx-auto news-article-body"><div class="rich-text"><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><strong>Tell us a little bit about yourself. How did you find your way to Condé Nast?</strong></span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">I have been working in human resources since I graduated from college, almost 20 years ago and joined Condé Nast China 15 years ago. At that time, our business and the team in the China Market was gradually expanding since it was established in 2005. I got the opportunity to join the people team in the Shanghai office and have been working here ever since.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><strong>How do you describe your job to friends and family?</strong></span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">I am responsible for all things related to people☺</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><strong>Lunar New Year is approaching soon, what does this holiday mean to you and how do you plan to celebrate?</strong>&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">A key word of Chinese Spring Festival to celebrate Lunar New Year is reunion. We usually have a nice family dinner with our parents and siblings on New Year’s Eve to share all expectations and meaningful things throughout the year. I will continue with this tradition for Lunar New Year!</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><strong>Reflecting on 2023, what is a project that you worked on that you are most proud of?&nbsp;</strong></span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">In 2023, Condé Nast China kicked off our top talent project. As a human resources business partner, I worked with different departments to identify each team's top talents and participated in discussions to promote the talent development plan. This is a very important project for the company to retain and develop talents. I am very proud to be part of it.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><strong>What is something you would like to do more of in 2024?</strong></span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">From the company's perspective, we hope to have more outputs in new businesses. I hope that I can assist business departments achieve this goal successfully.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><strong>As part of the HR team, how does Condé Nast China attract and retain top talent in the competitive media landscape?</strong></span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">We keep paying attention to both internal and external benchmarks so that we can maintain a competitive position in the market.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;"><strong>How does Condé Nast China foster a diverse and inclusive workplace? Could you share any stories to the global Condé Nast community?</strong></span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">In November of 2023, we were providing our managers with the training and resources to enact behavioral change, build empathy and ensure a workplace where we all treat each other with dignity and respect.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">We arranged two inclusive leadership offline training workshops for all leaders and managers in the Beijing and Shanghai offices in China. It was the first time we launched the diversity and inclusion (D&amp;I) offline training in the China market. The workshop was very successful and teams expressed their thoughts and understanding on D&amp;I in an open and trusting environment. People received more in-depth knowledge of the importance of diversity and inclusion and had more insights about how diversity fosters innovation and creates high-performing teams.</span></p></div></div></article></main></div><div><footer id="footer" class="jsx-d4ca4a36817c2f3e px-4 py-4 md:px-6 md:py-6 block bg-near-black"><section class="jsx-d4ca4a36817c2f3e border-b border-dark-border pt-12 mb-8 overflow-x-auto"><div class="jsx-d4ca4a36817c2f3e snap-mandatory snap-x flex overflow-nav-group"><div class="jsx-d4ca4a36817c2f3e inline-block pb-4 item text-yellow-200"><a class="mr-8 font-label hover:opacity-50 transition-opacity duration-300" href="/about">About</a></div><div class="jsx-d4ca4a36817c2f3e inline-block pb-4 item text-yellow-200"><a class="mr-8 font-label hover:opacity-50 transitio